This is an existing code, but the max length of a Java array is 2^31-1 (i.e. Integer.MAX_VALUE), which is the same as INT_MAX in C, is that correct? So this could be simplified into:
buffer_length = (*env)->GetArrayLength(env, buf);

No need to use real_length and max_length.

